Under the experimental conditions, the Abs working curve of the CDAu-Apt-As3+-glucose-AgNO3 system was draw as in Fig. 8
                        . With the increase of As3+ concentration (CAs), the absorption value of the system at 420 nm also gradually increased. The linear range (LR) was 0.025–0.75 μg/L As3+. The linear regression equation is ΔA420nm = 0.989 CAs + 0.028; the linear correlation coefficient is 0.9915 and the detection limit (DL) is 0.01 μg/L. This SPR absorption method was compared to some reported methods [31–34], It was not only highly sensitive but also very low-cost, simple and facile (Table 1
                        ).
